<paragraph id="94032055C3C015E792E9A111BBF3ECFD" pageId="0" pageNumber="203">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7F7B54042422EA20F09088990A913F4A" pageId="0" pageNumber="203">
<taxonomicName id="C71D430FD1206112BEB480F180EC13C8" authorityName="Y. H. Tan, M. B. Maw &amp; H. B. Ding" authorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Begonia putaoensis" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="203" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="putaoensis">
<emphasis id="E99BE2E2A88501A0C4A79BB8461D287A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="203">Begonia putaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Y.H. Tan, M.B. Maw &amp; H.B. Ding is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="2C049B3832E07C9A9534151A86FBC179" genus="B." lsidName="B. scintillans" pageId="0" pageNumber="203" rank="species" species="scintillans">
<emphasis id="F08220C5479F0D139A138EFA809A77DF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="203">B. scintillans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation id="5E2F22E352C0E4D51561F6343E5E5D16" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4120224" author="Dunn, ST" journalOrPublisher="Wageningen Agricultural University Papers" pageId="0" pageNumber="203" refId="B4" refString="Dunn, ST, 1920. Decades Kewensis: Plantarum Novarum in Herbario Horti Regii Conservatarum. Decas XCVI. Bulletin of Miscellaneous Information, Kew, 108-111. https://doi.org/10.2307/4120224" title="Decades Kewensis: Plantarum Novarum in Herbario Horti Regii Conservatarum. Decas XCVI. Bulletin of Miscellaneous Information, Kew, 108 - 111." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4120224" year="1920">Dunn (1920</bibRefCitation>
: 111) in rhizomatous creeping habit and dark green ovate leaves with silver or white area on the upper surface, but it can be easily distinguished by the following characters: sparsely pubescent adaxially leaf (
<emphasis id="2398035CB29F6B859CB6C8189F5F8A6F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="203">vs.</emphasis>
densely strigose) and glabrous capsule (
<emphasis id="F31C7DC85A803FCD242D7024A4F49E23" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="203">vs.</emphasis>
red villose).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
